# =============================================================================
# THE WEIGHT OF OFFICE: LBJ 1963–1969
# File: lbj_congress.dry
# Purpose: Congressional relations — the art of the deal, the limits
#          of the deal, and what happens when the deal runs out.
#
# DESIGN NOTES:
#   LBJ was the greatest Senate operator of the 20th century.
#   These cards should feel like that — the specific pleasure and
#   cost of working a legislative body you understand in your bones.
#
#   But there's a clock. The landslide of '64 gives him a supermajority
#   that can pass anything. The '66 midterms take 47 seats. After that,
#   the math changes. These cards reflect that arc.
#
#   Mechanically, Congress touches:
#     - lbj_capital (legislation costs it; wins restore it)
#     - lbj_credibility (broken promises cost it)
#     - lbj_approval (popular legislation raises it)
#     - lbj_gs_progress (bills passed)
#     - lbj_dixiecrats, lbj_liberals (factional management)
#     - lbj_unity (the country watches what Congress does)
#
#   The '66 midterms fire as a scripted event in November 1966.
#   After that, several cards gain new branches reflecting
#   the harder math of a thinner majority.
# =============================================================================

